Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update package lists and install required software
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3-pip \
        curl \
        ca-certificates

    # Install pytest for the forthcoming automated tests
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial filesystem state for the credential-rotation task
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    mkdir -p /home/user/credential_rotation

    # new_token.txt  – exactly one newline at the end
    printf 'SECURE-TOKEN-998877\n' > /home/user/credential_rotation/new_token.txt

    # fake_endpoint.json – valid JSON followed by exactly one newline
    cat <<'EOF' > /home/user/credential_rotation/fake_endpoint.json
{
  "result": "success"
}
EOF

    # Ensure world-readable permissions (no need for write access by learners)
    chmod 755 /home/user
    chmod 755 /home/user/credential_rotation
    chmod 644 /home/user/credential_rotation/new_token.txt
    chmod 644 /home/user/credential_rotation/fake_endpoint.json

%labels
    Author  credential-rotation-setup
    Description "Environment for API credential rotation exercise"

%help
This container provides the initial state for the “credential rotation” exercise.

Inside the container you will find:
  /home/user/credential_rotation/
      ├── new_token.txt        (contains the new bearer token)
      └── fake_endpoint.json   (mock API response)

Your task, as described in the assignment, is to read the token,
perform a single curl request against the local JSON file using the
Authorization header, and write the required two-line log file
rotation_check.log in the same directory.

pytest is pre-installed so the automated grader can verify your work.